<P>So the new Cardinall, for avoiding of contention, u&s;es to give the &s;aid three hun|dred and &s;eventy duckets to the Ma&s;ters of the Ceremonies, who&s;e care it is to di|&s;tribute them. And to the participant &s;e|cret Chamberlaines is given by the Cardi|nall which is pre&s;ent in <HI>Rome</HI> at his crea|tion, five hundred duckets at the lea&s;t; and by him, who out of <HI>Rome</HI> receives the Hatt, is given to them, be&s;ides the thou&s;and duckets due for the Hatt, other three hun|dred duckets: But Cardinalls which are Princes, doe give betwixt five and &s;ixe thou&s;and duckets, as al&s;o good rewards to the Ma&s;ters of the Popes Cardinalle Ne|phewes chamber:</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="part">
<PB N="125" REF="68">
<HEAD>The chief Cathedrall Churches of the &s;ix Bi&s;hops Cardinals are the&s;e.</HEAD>
<P><HI>OStia Porto,</HI> whereunto is adjoyned the Church of <HI>Santa Rufina, Albano, Sa|bina, Pale&s;trina,</HI> and <HI>Fra&s;cati.</HI></P>
</DIV2>
